content: What values are most important to me in life, and am I living in alignment with them?
What would I do differently if I knew nobody would judge me?
What recurring patterns in my life might be holding me back from growth?
When do I feel most truly myself, and what circumstances bring that out?
What fears have prevented me from pursuing what I truly want?
How have my biggest challenges shaped who I am today?
What does 'success' truly mean to me, beyond societal expectations?
What aspects of myself do I struggle to accept, and why?
How do I typically respond to stress, and are there healthier ways to cope?
What relationships in my life bring out the best version of me?
What would I want to be remembered for at the end of my life?
When do I feel most at peace, and how can I incorporate more of that into my daily life?
What limiting beliefs about myself do I need to let go of?
How has my definition of happiness evolved over time?
What parts of myself have I neglected that deserve attention?
What conversations have I been avoiding that I need to have?
How do I balance taking care of others with taking care of myself?
What lessons have my failures taught me that success never could?
What does my inner critic sound like, and how can I be kinder to myself?
If I had one year left to live, what would I change about how I'm living now?
